description.narrative: This award strives to help nations achieve sustainable improvements in the well-being and productivity of their populations through effective and accountable investments in education and other social services. This includes Global Education Framework (GEF) - Create Enabling Classroom Environment: Funds used to support creating an enabling classroom environment for improved reading and learning activities.. Global Education Framework (GEF) - Mozambique - Engaging Communities to Improve Early Grade Reading: Funds used to strengthen parental and community engagement in literacy activities to improve students’ early grade reading outcomes.. Global Education Framework (GEF) - Promoting Gender across Sectors-Safe Schools III: Funds used to conduct gender-related trainings and technical assistance with Volunteers and work partners, and implement the training packages developed under the Safe Sc. Global Education Framework (GEF) - Literacy Specialist: Funds used to provide for update and creation of training materials to carry out life skills and leadership youth activities.. Global Education Framework (GEF) - Philippines - Papayon Mindanao Project: Funds used for activities to improve youth literacy and life skills to support peace-building in Mindanao through learning camps and exchanges. The target populations are youth and. Global Education Framework (GEF) - Regional Literacy Trainings: Funds used to support a literacy specialist to provide technical support, advice, and training materials to the field to help improve early grade reading and youth literacy.. Global Education Framework (GEF) - Philippines - Papayon Mindanao Project: Funds used for activities to improve youth literacy and life skills to support peace-building in Mindanao through learning camps and exchanges.. Global Education Framework (GEF) - Promoting Gender across Sectors-Safe Schools III: Funds used to conduct gender-related trainings and technical assistance with Volunteers and work partners under the Safe Schools I.. Global Education Framework (GEF) - Regional Literacy Trainings: Funds used to support a literacy specialist to provide to help improve early grade reading and youth literacy.. Global Education Framework (GEF) - Uganda - Mobilizing Schools and Communities for Reading Project: Funds used to promote literacy at the primary level. Through camps, clubs and other activities, they will mobilize youth and communities to support reading. Global Education Framework (GEF) - Promoting Gender across Sectors-Safe Schools II: Funds used to expand efforts in gender training and gender technical assistance; to conduct gender-related trainings and technical assistance with Volunteers and counterpa.

To help nations achieve sustainable improvements in the well-being and productivity of their populations through effective and accountable investments in education and other social services. Promote equitable, effective, accountable, and sustainable formal and non-formal education systems.
